[meta-]
domain: podweb.info
author: Manuel Geissberger
[-meta]

[h1] About Podweb

[h2] Why?

[p-]
The web outside is a bit broken. Ads, trackers, paywalls, dark patterns.
Podweb is an experiment in something smaller and friendlier - a tiny web
that lives entirely inside Picotron, built on podnet.
[-p]

[h2] The format

[p-]
Pages are plain text files with a simple tag system. Tags like h1, h2
and p handle structure. Block tags wrap across multiple lines. Everything
is hand-written and human-readable.
[-p]

[h2] The browser

[p-]
This browser fetches .podweb files from podnet, parses the tags and
renders them. It is itself a Picotron cart - a p64 file you can read,
modify and redistribute.
[-p]

[link file=index.podweb] Back to home
